A political alliance that will bring on board like minded leaders, ahead of the 2022 presidential race might be in the pipe line with a section of leaders hinting during various weekend meetings and rallies over the weekend. Siaya Senator, James Orengo dropped a bomb shell on Saturday while in Kakamega county, sentiments that were backed by a number of leaders from the ODM party that President Uhuru Kenyatta and former PM Raila Odinga will form a formidable force, that might bring on board Musalia Mudavadi and Gideon Moi ahead of the 2022 polls. 